body:
You are designing an editorial-quality vertical infographic.

CONTENT BRIEF
- Topic / subject: {{topic}}
- Main title: {{title}}
- Number of sections / items to visualize: {{section_count}}
- Section labels (one per line, optional): {{section_labels}}

DESIGN DIRECTION
- Layout pattern: {{layout}}
- Tone: {{tone}}
- Color palette: {{color_palette}}

DESIGN RULES
- Aspect: 2:3 vertical (~1024×1536), print-ready
- Information hierarchy: title > section headers > body labels > supporting details
- Each section visually distinct yet part of one cohesive system (consistent icons, line weights, type)
- Use real visual content per section (illustrated icons, mini-diagrams, photographic insets) — never placeholder boxes
- Generous gutters; the page must breathe; avoid wall-to-wall text
- Style: museum / encyclopedia / annual-report polish — Information is Beautiful, Edward Tufte, MUJI catalogues
- All labels must be crisp, correctly spelled, and legible at thumbnail size
- Avoid: clipart icons, generic stock graphics, AI-style watercolor smears, low-contrast text-on-photo

If a field is empty or "—", infer the most tasteful default for the topic.
